cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about language models (LMs) that integrate discrete and neural features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for language modeling, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper uses statistical methods to evaluate the performance of the models, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
